source.name: Veterans Health Administration 2008 Hospital Report Card - Nosocomial Infections
source.description: Report to the Appropriations Committee of the United States House of Representatives in Response to Conference Committee Report to PL 110-186.  In an effort to provide a snapshot of the quality of care provided at VA health care facilities, this report includes information about waiting times, staffing level, infection rates, surgical volumes, quality measures, patient satisfaction, service availability and complexity, accreditation status, and patient safety. The data in this report have been drawn from multiple sources across VHA.  This dataset contains the data about Central Line Infections and Ventilator Associated Pnemonia.
